OL,4,CChelsea's Ivy Asia restaurant sorry for
OL,5,C'culturally insensitive' advert
OL,6, A restaurant has apologised for a
OL,7, "culturally insensitive" ad campaign.
OL,9,FThe Ivy Asia in Chelsea, west London,
OL,10,Fposted a video on social media which
OL,11,Ffeatured women dressed as geishas being
OL,12,Fpulled in a rickshaw to the restaurant.
OL,14,FFood writer Jay Rayner was among the
OL,15,Fadvert's many critics, describing it as
OL,16,F"premeditated racist stereotyping". The
OL,17,Fvideo has since been deleted.
OL,19,FThe Ivy chain, best known for its
OL,20,Foriginal restaurant in Soho, said it
OL,21,Fwas conducting an internal review.
